						<summary>

						<p>One of the fragments refers to an endowment of a hundred and odd <hi rend="italic">(•• ttara-śata) nishkas,</hi> another to a gift of sheep, the third to a gift of buffaloes and the fourth to a gift of land. The fragments are in characters of about the 13th century A.D.</p>						

